T1  - Morular metaplasia of the endometrium in a patient with polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Ryuko K.
A1  - Miura H.
A1  - Iwanari O.
A1  - Abu-Musa A.
A1  - Kitao M. 
Y1  - 1993//
N2  - A 31-year-old women with polycystic ovary syndrome underwent dilatation and curettage (D and C) as part of her infertility workup. Pathologic examination revealed endometrial morular metaplasia without malignant potential. Follow-up D and C had no evidence of endometrial hyperplasia or carcinoma. The diagnostic difficulties and pathogenesis are discussed.
