N2  - A case of mullerian adenosarcoma of the uterus with sarcomatous overgrowth is described. The patient was also found to have bilateral polycystic ovaries. This 25 year-old white female presented with irregular vaginal bleeding and was diagnosed as having mullerian adenosarcoma with sarcomatous overgrowth by dilatation, curettage, and biopsy. Total abdominal hysterectomy, bilateral salpingo-oophorectomy with lymph node sampling were performed.
