8231. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 20316453
ID  - 2102331 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2102331]
T1  - Polycystic ovarian disease
A1  - Fox R. 
Y1  - 1990//
N2  - Polycystic ovarian disease (PCOD), the most common cause of ovulatory disorder and idiopathic hirsutism, remains difficult both to treat reliably and to understand. In this review, in addition to a practical discussion of diagnosis and treatment, I focus attention on the nature of PCOD, highlighting aspects of pathogenesis that hold the key to improved management. The polycystic ovary is but one sign of a wide-ranging disorder with implications for general well-being, perhaps of greater importance than the more easily recognized gynecologic complications.
